The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Wednesday, April 28, 2004 				 Six dropped for dodging poll duty 
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, April 27: The West Midnapore district administration has suspended six employees and handed showcause notices to 300 for not accepting poll duties, additional district magistrate Syedul Islam said today.																								The chief electoral officer said he had no details, but added, we have told officials to take very strict action.																								Ramps would be installed at all polling premises in urban areas, including Calcutta, for the disabled, Basudeb Banerjee said. An 80-year-old north Calcutta resident had called the Election Commission saying he would have problems going to the booth. Banerjee said an ambulance would be arranged for him.																								Banerjee said a revised voters list would have 40,000 to 50,000 names less as those of the dead and whose names appeared twice have been deleted. Banerjees name was included twice as he had shifted residence from Dhakuria to Salt Lake.
